<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>

<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="oa-3-1-shoes-socks">
    <statement>
        <p>
            A very useful idea whenever we talk about solving is the <term>shoes and socks principle</term>, which we'll explore in this activity.
        </p>
        <p>
            Bleepblorp the friendly alien has arrived on our planet, and is interested in human footwear.
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Write Bleepblorp a set of careful, step-by-step instructions about how to put on shoes and socks.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Oh no! Bleepblorp absolutely hates wearing shoes and socks! Write Bleepblorp a set of careful, step-by-step instructions about how to <em>remove</em> the footwear.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    What do you notice about the steps in your putting-on instructions vs. the steps in your removing instructions?
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</exploration>